Description: This is a Fender Limited Edition Parallel Universe American Elite Nashville Telecaster. The guitar is in fantastic condition. Honestly, you can buy a brand new one (if you can find one) but I doubt you could tell the difference from this one. This guitar is virtually unused. Solidbody Electric Guitar with Ash Body, Maple Neck, Maple Fingerboard, 1 Humbucking Pickup, and 2 Single-coil Pickups, and a beautiful aged cherry burst finish. Also features a direct-mounted ShawBucker humbucking bridge pickup, along with pair of Pure Vintage ’64 Tele pickups in the middle position and neck positions give this guitar a uniquely powerful voice. Designed for enhanced playing feel and speed, the compound “C-to-D” shaped neck sports a fast 9.5”-14” compound-radius fingerboard, medium jumbo frets and a bone nut. Polished chrome-plated brass saddles adorn the hardtail bridge and the headstock wears an old-school silver Fender logo—aesthetic touches that give it a touch of class.
